jaccard_index_allyears <- readRDS(here::here("output","jaccard_index_VEGAN", "jaccard_index_allyears.rds"))

#make survey and survey unit factors
jaccard_index_allyears[,survey:=factor(survey)][,survey_unit:=factor(survey_unit)]

#adjust years
jaccard_index_allyears[,year_adj := year-min(year)+1]

#add new variable for year in sequence per region
jaccard_index_allyears[,first_year := min(year),.(survey_unit)]
jaccard_index_allyears[,last_year := max(year),.(survey_unit)]

#jaccard_index_allyears[,year_in_seq := year-first_year+1]

jaccard_index_allyears[,years_sampled := last_year-first_year+1]

##Linear Model

Also, build a simple linear model with an interaction (instead of random slope and intercept for survey) THIS IS HOW WE CLASSIFY SURVEYS as of fall 2023 (update from before, where we classified surveys from LMER) (Especially good because lmer didnât converge)


jaccard_total_lm <- lm(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year * survey_unit,data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == "jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary"])

#alternative, what if we use GLS (allows us to include temporal autocorrelation term)
jaccard_total_gls <- gls(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year * survey_unit,correlation = corAR1(form=~year | survey_unit),data = jaccard_index_allyears[dissimilarity_metric == "jaccard_dissimilarity_index_binary"])

#compare these two models
AICc(jaccard_total_lm, jaccard_total_gls)

jaccard_total_coefs.r <- data.table(lm_interaction_coefficients_se(jaccard_total_lm))

#Add survey names
jaccard_total_coefs.r[,survey_unit := sort(unique(jaccard_index_allyears$survey_unit))]
  
  #Homogenizing vs differentiating
  jaccard_total_coefs.r[,differentiating := ifelse((se< abs(estimate) & estimate > 0),1,0)][,homogenizing := ifelse((se< abs(estimate) & estimate < 0),1,0)]
  
  #lower and upper CI
    jaccard_total_coefs.r[,lwr := estimate-se][,upr:= estimate + se]
    
    #save as output
    fwrite(jaccard_total_coefs.r, here::here("output","jaccard_total_coefs.r.csv"))
  
  jaccard_total_coefs_sum <- data.table(differentiating = sum(  jaccard_total_coefs.r$differentiating), homogenizing = sum(  jaccard_total_coefs.r$homogenizing))
  
  #hex by trend
  jaccard_total_coefs.r[,trend_color_jaccard := ifelse(homogenizing == 1,"#FFC109", ifelse(differentiating == 1,"#D81C60","#1E88E5"))]
  
  #link to color link
  jaccard_total_coefs.r <- color_link[jaccard_total_coefs.r, on = "survey_unit"]
  
  color_link_trend_jaccard <- jaccard_total_coefs.r[,.(survey_unit,Survey_Name_Season, hex,  trend_color_jaccard)]

##Wavy Line Plot for GAMs (Figure 2a)

Generate predicted values (this datatable will hold all jaccard metrics)

#generate list again, as for some reason it doesn't stay in environment
survey_unit.list <- levels(factor(jaccard_index_allyears$survey_unit))

#generate new data to smooth lines (need year and season survey combinations)
year_survey_unit_expand.dt <- data.table(survey_unit = as.character(NULL), year = as.numeric(NULL), year_adj = as.numeric(NULL ))

for (i in 1:length(survey_unit.list)) {
  #generate year vectors
  survey_unit_years <- unique(jaccard_index_allyears[survey_unit == survey_unit.list[i],.(survey_unit, year, year_adj)])
  
  years <- seq(min(survey_unit_years[,year]), max(survey_unit_years[,year]), by = 0.1)
  
  year_adjust <- seq(min(survey_unit_years[,year_adj]), max(survey_unit_years[,year_adj]), by = 0.1)
  
  year_survey_unit_expand.dt_addition <- data.table(survey_unit = survey_unit.list[i], year = years, year_adj = year_adjust)
  
  year_survey_unit_expand.dt <- rbind(year_survey_unit_expand.dt, year_survey_unit_expand.dt_addition)
}


#add colors and names to full year and survey unit combination table
year_survey_unit_expand_jaccard.dt <- year_survey_unit_expand.dt[color_link_trend_jaccard, on = "survey_unit"]

Jaccard Get model as predictions

#for plotting, get model as predictions
jaccard_total_gam_predictions <- predict(jaccard_total_gam, se.fit = TRUE, newdata = year_survey_unit_expand_jaccard.dt)

###Is each survey better described by LM or by GAM? ####Also, compile predicted values from GAM ####Jaccard


#list of surveys
survey_unit.list_jaccard <- levels(factor(jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard$survey_unit))

# Function to compare GAM and linear model fits
compare_models <- function(subset_data) {
  # Fit GAM model with "fs" basis and single smooth term
  gam_model <- gam(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ s(year, bs = "fs", m = 1), data = subset_data)
  
  # Fit linear model
  lm_model <- lm(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ year, data = subset_data)
  
  # Calculate AICc values
  aicc_gam <- AICc(gam_model)
  aicc_lm <- AICc(lm_model)
  
  #Calculate p-values
  gam_pvalue <- summary(gam_model)$s.table[1,4]
  lm_pvalue <- summary(lm_model)$coefficients[2,4]
  
  comparison <- ifelse((abs(aicc_gam-aicc_lm) < 2 | (aicc_gam == aicc_lm)),"Same",
                       ifelse(((abs(aicc_gam-aicc_lm) > 2 & (aicc_gam < aicc_lm))),"GAM",
                              ifelse(((abs(aicc_gam-aicc_lm) > 2 & (aicc_gam > aicc_lm))), "Linear",NA)))
  
   return(data.table(Survey = unique(subset_data$Survey_Name_Season)[1],
                     survey_unit = unique(subset_data$survey_unit),
                    comparison = comparison,
                    aicc_gam = aicc_gam,
                    gam_p = gam_pvalue,
                    aicc_lm = aicc_lm,
                    lm_p = lm_pvalue))
}


############## Compare models for each survey name and bind the results
GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total <- data.table()

for (i in 1:length(survey_unit.list_jaccard)) {
  GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total_single <- compare_models(jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit == survey_unit.list_jaccard[i],])
  GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total <- rbind(GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total, GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total_single)
}

GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total

#round to 2 significant figures

#names of numeric columns
numeric_cols <- names(GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total)[sapply(GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total, is.numeric)]

# Apply signif() only to numeric columns
GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total[, (numeric_cols) := lapply(.SD, function(x) if (is.numeric(x)) signif(x, digits = 3) else x), .SDcols = numeric_cols]

GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total.f <- GAM_LM_model_comparisons_jaccard_total[,-2]

##################generate predicted GAM values
GAM_outputs <- function(subset.data) {
# Fit GAM model with "fs" basis and single smooth term
  gam_model <- gam(annual_dissimilarity_value ~ s(year, bs = "fs", m = 1), data = subset.data)
  
  pred_values <- predict(gam_model, se.fit = T)
  pred_table <- data.table(year = subset.data$year, predicted_dissimilarity = as.numeric(pred_values$fit), predicted_lwr = as.numeric(pred_values$fit)-as.numeric(pred_values$se.fit), predicted_upr = as.numeric(pred_values$fit)+as.numeric(pred_values$se.fit))
  
  st_dev_pred_dissim <- sd(pred_table$predicted_dissimilarity)
  return(signif(st_dev_pred_dissim,2))
}

predicted_values_jaccard <- data.table(survey_unit = survey_unit.list_jaccard, SD_pred_dissim = as.numeric())
Warning: Item 2 has 0 rows but longest item has 34; filled with NA

  st_dev_pred_dissim <- GAM_outputs(jaccard_index_allyears_jaccard[survey_unit == survey_unit.list_jaccard[i]])
  predicted_values_jaccard[i,"SD_pred_dissim"] <- st_dev_pred_dissim
}
